    <p>Academy is a part of the consulting company Academic Work with a concept to fulfil the competence needs of the market, using a concept of accelerated learning. One of those programs teaches programming with the object-oriented language C# on the .NET Framework during a 12-week time span. The program has the goal that the participants will become IT consultants [1]. The course ends with a 2 week final project, where the knowledge obtained during the course is applied.</p>
    <p>The purpose of the final project is to link together the techniques and subjects that the participants have been in touch with, in an aspect of Personal Development. Furthermore, the consultant is supposed to apply those techniques and skills obtained during the course together within a project [2].</p>
    <p>This final project of Academy accelerated learning in C# HT17 was created between the fourth and fifteenth of December 2017, during the last two weeks of the course. The goal with WindCatchaz is to create a project dedicated to presenting the speeds and routes of sailboats by retrieving weather data from an external source like SMHI [3] and calculate how long this trip will take based on defined values from a Velocity Prediction Program, compared to the relative direction of the sailboat.</p>
    <p>
        The result is an MVC with the following features:
        <ul>
            <li>Create a map and load weather data (and show wind directions)</li>
            <li>Let the user choose a starting point and a destination point (and a departure time) and store coordinates for latitude and longitude </li>
            <li>Calculate the distance</li>
            <li>Retrievs real data from SMHI</li>
            <li>Animated overlay of the winddirections</li>
            <li>Create account</li>
            <li>Login</li>
            <li>Validation</li>
            <li>Use some simple interpolation to calculate the velocity for those wind speeds that are not in the VPP</li>
            <li>Calculate the time it will take to go from the starting point to the goal (with penalty for tacking)</li>
            <li>Let the user create their own VPP and edit those based on experience</li>
            <li>Let the user only decide a few values in the VPP and use interpolation to fill in the gaps</li>
            <li>About view page with information of the project</li>
        </ul>
    </p>
