    <h2>3. Goal</h2>
    <p>This final project of Academy accelerated learning in C# HT17 was created between the fourth and fifteenth of December 2017, during the last two weeks of the course. The goal with WindCatchaz is to create a project dedicated to presenting the speeds and routes of sailboats by retrieving weather data from an external source like SMHI [3] and calculate how long this trip will take based on defined values from a VPP, Velocity Prediction Program, compared to the relative direction of the sailboat.</p>

